-- Barca, Atletico Stay Perfect in Spanish Soccer; Marseille Wins
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-09-25T00:14:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-25/barca-atletico-stay-perfect-in-spanish-soccer-marseille-wins.html
Barcelona and Atletico Madrid won
at home to maintain their perfect starts in Spanish soccer’s La
Liga, while Marseille moved level with French leader Monaco.  Brazilian strikerNeymarscored his first league goal for
Barca as the Catalan club beat Real Sociedad 4-1 last night to
tie its best start to a season with six straight wins.  Lionel Messi ,  Sergio Busquets  and Marc Bartra added the other goals.  Diego Costa scored twice in the opening 25 minutes as
Atletico defeated Osasuna 2-1 to join defending champion Barca
atop the standings with 18 points.  Marseille ended a three-game winless run in France’s Ligue
1 by beating Saint-Etienne 2-1 to pull even on 14 points with
Monaco, which hosts Bastia today. Lille moved up to third place
with a 3-0 home win against Evian.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
